### 4. 🟡 Stream Initialization: Stale cleanup race in [useStreamClient](file:///c:/Users/asmit/Desktop/SEM%206%20Project/talent-IQ/frontend/src/hooks/useStreamClient.js#7-90)

**File:** [useStreamClient.js](file:///c:/Users/asmit/Desktop/SEM%206%20Project/talent-IQ/frontend/src/hooks/useStreamClient.js#L14-L80)

**Problem:** If the `useEffect` re-fires (e.g., session refetch changes dependencies) before the async [initCall](file:///c:/Users/asmit/Desktop/SEM%206%20Project/talent-IQ/frontend/src/hooks/useStreamClient.js#18-64) completes, there's no cancellation flag. The old async call will still set state on an unmounted/re-rendered component, and the cleanup only cleans up the *local* `videoCall`/`chatClientInstance` variables — which are still `null` because init didn't finish yet.

**Fix:** Add a `cancelled` flag so stale async calls don't set state.

```diff
  useEffect(() => {
    let videoCall = null;
    let chatClientInstance = null;
+   let cancelled = false;

    const initCall = async () => {
      // ... guards ...
      try {
        // ... init code ...
+       if (cancelled) return;
        setStreamClient(client);
        // ... more init ...
+       if (cancelled) return;
        setCall(videoCall);
        // ... chat init ...
+       if (cancelled) return;
        setChatClient(chatClientInstance);
        setChannel(chatChannel);
      } catch (error) { ... }
    };

    return () => {
+     cancelled = true;
      // ... existing cleanup ...
    };
  }, [...]);
```

