### 6. 🟡 `meetingId` uniqueness collision on creation

**File:** [sessionController.js](file:///c:/Users/asmit/Desktop/SEM%206%20Project/talent-IQ/backend/src/controllers/sessionController.js#L4-L8)

**Problem:** [generateMeetingId](file:///c:/Users/asmit/Desktop/SEM%206%20Project/talent-IQ/backend/src/controllers/sessionController.js#4-9) uses `Math.random()`. If two sessions are created at the exact same time and happen to generate the same 9-digit number, the MongoDB `unique` index will throw a duplicate key error, returning a generic 500 to the user.

**Fix:** Add a retry loop in [createSession](file:///c:/Users/asmit/Desktop/SEM%206%20Project/talent-IQ/frontend/src/api/sessions.js#4-8) when meeting ID collision occurs.

```diff
+ let meetingId;
+ let retries = 3;
+ while (retries > 0) {
+   meetingId = generateMeetingId();
+   const exists = await Session.findOne({ meetingId });
+   if (!exists) break;
+   retries--;
+ }
+ if (retries === 0) {
+   return res.status(500).json({ message: "Failed to generate unique meeting ID, please try again" });
+ }
```

